Ecology. Specimens from Chukotka and Yukon Territory were collected in stony habitats. In Iowa , one male was collected in algific talus slope developed in limestone and one in a cave. It is in coincidence with the knowledge that lithobiontic species colonise more cold habitats (such as freezing scree slopes and caves) in warmer parts of their distribution area ( Růžička 1990 , 2011 ;
Růžička et al. 2012
).
